article.description: Nathan Dieudonne had a key jumper and steal to help Boston University pull away midway in the second half and beat Quinnipiac 64-57 on Sunday.
article.headline: BU rallies midway through 2nd half, beats Quinnipiac 64-57
article.linkText: BU rallies midway through 2nd half, beats Quinnipiac 64-57
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- Nathan Dieudonne had a key jumper and steal to help Boston University pull away midway in the second half and beat Quinnipiac 64-57 on Sunday. Dieudonne had four steals, six rebounds and chipped in eight points. Cheddi Mosely, John Papale and Eric Fanning scored 13 points each to lead Boston University (5-5). Giovanni McLean scored 24 points on 9-of-19 shooting to lead Quinnipiac (4-5). Donovan Smith added 14 points. Quinnipiac led 47-34 with 14 minutes left. Papale made two 3-pointers during a 14-3 surge to pull BU to 50-48. Dieudonne scored to tie it at 50, and then forced a Smith turnover. Fanning made a pair of free throws, Dieudonne had a layup, and Kyle Foreman made a 3-pointer and the Terriers led 57-50 with five minutes remaining. McLean made a 3 to pull Quinnipiac to 60-57 with 1:29 left. The Bobcats missed six shots and had two turnovers to seal it.
